fields.name: Samsung Galaxy A54
fields.description:
Awesome Camera - Capture crisp shots every time with the triple-lens floating camera design, allowing you to switch between a suite of lenses, including a wide 50 mega pixel and ultra-wide 12 mega pixel main camera to shoot magnificent landscapes an intense 5 mega pixel macro lens for the tiniest details plus the impressive font-facing camera to snap studio quality selfies. The photos don’t have to end when the night starts because the optical image stabilisation and bigger sensor will capture all your moves.
Awesome Infinity-O Display - Enjoy a 6.4 inch Full HD+ screen** equipped with 120 hertz refresh rate, perfect for oh-so smooth scrolling, gaming and multi-tasking without interruption. Experience everything you love and see it in vibrant true-to-life colours with the impressive super AMOLED display technology that improves outdoor visibility.
Battery - Up to 2 Day Battery Life*** on the Galaxy A54 5G so you can freely connect, stream and share. Powerfully supported by 25W Super-Fast Charging so you won’t ever miss out.
Powerful performance - Galaxy A54 5G combines Octa-core processing power with 6GB of RAM built to enable lasting power and performance to help maximise speed, gaming, camera and so much more. Get access to seriously fast download and upload speeds with 5G technology. *
Wallet - Secure. Simple. Smart. Store payment cards, loyalty cards, digital IDs, passwords and even digital keys to your house all in one place. Easy to use and secured by your biometrics, it's all you need to leave home.
Security - Privacy is everything, so we built in high-tech biometric authentication through the on-screen fingerprint scanner and your sensitive information is protected by Samsung Knox security the moment it’s turned on.
Storage - Forget deleting, Galaxy A54 5G has spacious storage of up to 128GB. Plus experience the added option for expandable 1TB microSD support so you can focus on the now. ****
In-box items - Handset, data cable, ejection pin and quick start guide
*Available on selected plans on eligible 5G networks. Current availability is limited to major capital city CBDs and other select high traffic areas. Actual speeds achievable will vary depending on service availability and other factors.

fields.name: Apple Watch Series 8
fields.description:
WHY APPLE WATCH SERIES 8 — Your essential companion for a healthy life is now even more powerful. Advanced sensors provide insights to help you better understand your health. New safety features can get you help when you need it. The bright, Always-On Retina display is easy to read, even when your wrist is down.
EASILY CUSTOMIZABLE — Available in a range of sizes and materials, with dozens of bands to choose from and watch faces with complications tailored to whatever you’re into.
INNOVATIVE SAFETY FEATURES — Crash Detection and Fall Detection can automatically connect you with emergency services in the event of a severe car crash or a hard fall. And Emergency SOS provides urgent assistance with the press of a button.
ADVANCED HEALTH FEATURES — Temperature sensing is a breakthrough feature that provides deep insights into women’s health. Keep an eye on your blood oxygen. Take an ECG anytime. Get notifications if you have an irregular rhythm. And see how much time you spent in REM, Core, or Deep sleep with Sleep Stages.
SIMPLY COMPATIBLE — It works seamlessly with your Apple devices and services. Unlock your Mac automatically. Find your devices with a tap. Pay and send money with Apple Pay. Apple Watch requires an iPhone 8 or later with the latest iOS version.
INCREDIBLE DURABILITY — Tougher than tough. It’s crack resistant, IP6X-certified dust resistant, and swimproof with WR50 water resistance.
A POWERFUL FITNESS PARTNER — The enhanced Workout app gives you new ways to train, and advanced metrics for more information about your workout performance. And Apple Watch comes with three months of Apple Fitness+ free.
APPS ON YOUR WRIST — With access to tens of thousands of apps on the App Store right on your wrist, Apple Watch is the perfect personal device for whatever you love to do.
STAY CONNECTED — Send a text, make a call, listen to music and podcasts, use Siri, and get notifications on the go. Apple Watch Series 8 (GPS) works with your iPhone or Wi-Fi to keep you connected.

fields.title: Good
fields.review:
I didn't want to get a new iphone as my iphone 6+ was working fine except that it would not accept any of the latest iOS updates and that meant a lot of the apps were very slow or didn't work at all.
I took the plunge and got the new phone and I must say I'm very happy with it. The camera take much better photos than my iphone 6+ however I think the quality of the iphone 6+ photos had deteriorated dramatically over the years (more built-in obselescence??) The new phone is much faster. The size is good.

fields.title: Bad
fields.review: My first response is total disappointment as it is totally flat and there is no adapter to allow charging. As this has always been included I didn’t think I needed it and it is not clearly stated. Cheap strategy from Apple. Make sure you include a charging adapter.

fields.review: I did watch a couple if reviews online. Can’t go wrong with this one. Display is real nice, fluid operation and android updated. I did delete Samsung crap from it. Camera results are good too. I will recommend this device.

fields.title: Understated beauty
fields.review:
I bought the Apple Watch Series 8 (GPS + Cellular 45mm) Smart Watch to replace the smart watch I was using. I am simply in love with it and cannot understand why I hadn’t bought an Apple Watch before, I am most definitely a convert now. I bought the gold Milanese wrist band to go with it and absolutely love the ease of taking my watch on and off.
The fitness app is like someone nagging you to get up and move but in a good way. I could write lots about this watch (all good) but don’t have time so i will just like to say ‘no matter who you are you need an Apple watch’. Most definitely an A+ from me.

fields.title: Reasonable Sound, inconvenient design
fields.review:
Praise: The sound is reasonably good. The App is a nice touch and helpful in tweaking the sound.
Gripes : 1. The Squad / Green colour I wanted, is available only in certain countries. 2. The control buttons are rather inconveniently placed, out of direct sight, making one operate them by touch / feel or by guessing. 3. The buttons are an exact match ofthe body Colour and are difficult to see. These would have been better in a contrasting colour. 4. Connection issues: when I am playing music from my Tab S7 through the Flip 6 and try to connect my cell phone too, the tablet is paused and has to be manually restarted. Both devices Cannot connect to the speaker together.

fields.title: iPads have a good reputation but...
fields.review:
The iPad Mini 6th gen is an expensive device. My wife bought this for use with various reading Apps she has.

Complaints -

1. The screen quality is worse than her 6 year old Samsung Galaxy Tab S2 - that has an OLED screen at higher DPI. It has less contrast, muted colors and most noticeably terrible viewing angles. If you roll the tablet around while looking at it there is a clear hot-spot of brightness that shows immediately you tilt the tablet. Pretty terrible. To top it off - bad jelly scrolling.

2. The iOS operating system is infuriatingly inflexible. Don't expect to be arranging your icons as you see fit.

3. A few headline Apps like Instagram do not display correctly on this tablet. They are shrunken down and don't fill the screen correctly. Designed for iPhone only.

4. Incredibly expensive. Inc the pencil

... Apple is fortunate the Android competition has largely given up. If you take your time and really dig, you will find far superior alternatives (Screen, Flexibility etc) at a lower cost.
